On Thursday, April 15, 2004, at 12:24PM, Eron Crites <emcrites(-at-)msn.com> wrote:

>Cut corners?  Maybe...but it is more likely that he didn't chemically treat 
>the wheels before coating them.  Physical removal of rust on a visually 
>inspected basis is only half of the job.  On a molecular level, there is 
>still oxidation at work.  Without a zinc treatment of some sort, the cancer 
>will arise yet again!

I agree: blame the painter not the paint.

Sometimes parts to be powdercoated need to be prebaked so they don't outgas during the baking process leaving the item more susceptible to future rusting. 

